## Deterministic security gates (inner loop)

The mechanically detectable half of security never routes to an LLM judge — it runs as typed gates on
every commit, and findings are `product-defect` by construction:

```
secret_scan : {{SECRET_SCAN_CMD}}   # e.g. gitleaks protect --staged
sast        : {{SAST_CMD}}          # e.g. semgrep --config auto; "none" if deliberately not adopted
```

## How the workflow honors it

- **`/aep-build` Phase 6** — **journey-first**: Step A authors/extends the journey from the layer's
  acceptance criteria and commits it pre-merge (unless `dogfood_target == none`, where there is no runnable
  surface and every criterion is proven via Tier-1 / Tier-3). Step B then executes it: resolve the target
  from `dogfood_target` (`cli` → run the built binary via **bash**, no URL; `local` → `$BASE_URL`;
  `deployed:<url>` → that URL) and run the journey with the tool from
  [`tool-selection.md`](./tool-selection.md). With `journey_timing: post-deploy`, Step A still authors +
  commits the journey now; only Step B's execution is deferred to the layer gate.
- **`/aep-wrap` layer gate** — runs only the **applicable tiers**; with `journey_timing: post-deploy` it
  executes the journey against the `deployed:<url>` target after the merge/deploy, then flips
  `scripted_passed → passed`. It **executes, never authors** — **when Tier-2 is an applicable tier**
  (`applicable_tiers` includes `2`), a layer that reaches the gate with no journey file is a COVERAGE
  FAILURE (the build should have authored it) and stays `scripted_passed`. (A project without Tier-2 —
  `applicable_tiers` lacks `2`, e.g. an API-only `[1,3]` or a `none`-target `[1]` repo — has no journey by
  design and gates on its applicable tiers + coverage.) The gate runs the **target-bound preflight**
  first (REFUSED ≠ FAIL — a refusal pauses the gate with an ops checklist, spending nothing), honors
  `live_policy` for its live half, and flips `passed` only with at least one **tamper-evident evidence
  class** in the record.
- **`/aep-dispatch`** — blocks the next layer until the gate is `passed` under this policy (a
  `scripted_passed` gate still blocks: "machinery green, dogfood pending").

> Changing this policy is a deliberate act — it changes what "done" means for every layer. Re-run
> `/aep-e2e-skill-scaffolding`; it re-confirms with you and never silently rewrites your choices.
